<para> "So ... what about the music?" means that the professor wants to explore
the earlier topic of music further (A). This is a rhetorical question; therefore,
he is not trying to discover (find out) or elicit his students' responses
(B). <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> So </emphasis>here does not mean <emphasis
emphasis-type="italic"> therefore </emphasis>or <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> to</emphasis><emphasis
emphasis-type="italic"> summarize </emphasis>(C). The professor's tone is
confident, rather than unsure of his topic (D).</para>
